"{\"uid\": \"canberratimes.com.au-story-8759750-oarful-olympic-medals-stolen-from-rowing-legend-drew-ginn\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Your digital subscription includes access to content from all our websites in your region.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 90, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Access unlimited news content and The Canberra Times app.\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Canberra Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Premium subscribers also enjoy interactive puzzles and access to the digital version of our print edition - Today's Paper.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Police have arrested and charged a man following the alleged theft of four Olympic gold medals fromAustralian champion rower Drew Ginn.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Ginn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drew Ginn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Ginn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drew_Ginn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loginor signup to continue reading  Mr Ginn was a member of the Oarsome Foursome, a highly successful rowing crew, earning a gold medal at the 1996 Atlanta, 2004 Athens and 2008 Beijing Olympics as well as a silver medal at the 2012 London games.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999985024294191, \"rank\": 1.495774230417061e-06, \"text\": \"1996 Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 568, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999679525905, \"rank\": 3.1819981772480827e-08, \"text\": \"2004 Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999969163582, \"rank\": 3.0835544743141117e-09, \"text\": \"2012 London games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals, allegedly stolen from a black Land Rover parked in the inner-city Melbourne suburb of Docklands, were in Mr Ginn's car after a speaking engagement at a school, he told police.\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rover_Company\", \"score\": 0.989342063724127, \"rank\": 0.009649548723975531, \"text\": \"Rover\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rover_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rover_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999999618471528, \"rank\": 3.812476377248833e-08, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Docklands\", \"score\": 0.9999064591539562, \"rank\": 9.34427321640952e-05, \"text\": \"Docklands\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Docklands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Docklands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These are unbelievably rare items with significant sentimental value,\\\" detective sergeant Timothy Reiher said.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Timothy\", \"score\": 0.991838716229085, \"rank\": 0.007718055930968469, \"text\": \"Timothy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Timothy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Timothy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Olympic medals are awarded to the best of the best and are priceless to their recipients,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Investigators believe the thieves broke into the 49-year-old's car between 9pm on September 6 and 5am on September 7 while it was parked on Cumberland Street.\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Rip Curl wetsuit, a Go Pro camera and Sony headphones were also allegedly stolen.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rip_Curl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rip Curl\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rip_Curl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rip_Curl\"}, {\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sony\", \"score\": 0.9991449829794692, \"rank\": 0.0007708450798513645, \"text\": \"Sony\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We ask that people look out for these medals in pawn shops and online selling platforms,\\\" detective sergeant Reiher said.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On September 11, police said a 47-year-old Windsor man, who was wanted on warrant over the alleged offending, was arrested by police in Brunswick.\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has been charged with theft from motor vehicle, obtain property by deception, obtain financial advantage by deception and handle stolen goods, police said.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He will face Melbourne Magistrates' Court on November 29.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Magistrates'_Court\", \"score\": 0.9999991655689726, \"rank\": 8.344315330522479e-07, \"text\": \"Melbourne Magistrates' Court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Magistrates'_Court\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Magistrates'_Court\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neither the Olympic medals or any of the other allegedly stolen property has been recovered.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyone with information that could assist in locating the stolen medals is urged to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000 or make a report atwww.crimestoppersvic.com.au  Anna Houlahan reports on crime and social issues affecting regional and remote Australia in her role as national crime reporter at Australian Community Media (ACM).\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 2228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\", \"score\": 0.8463511728357758, \"rank\": 0.18150224336888304, \"text\": \"Anna\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\"}, {\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999978144842, \"rank\": 1.6423799066250112e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\"